         1. Hero Section: Summary of the research task and key constraints.
         2. Dashboard (Meta-Analysis): Interactive visualizations of the 5 requested tables (Frequency, Density, Profitable Niches, etc.).
         3. Directory (Core Feature): A searchable, filterable list of the 100 generated ideas. Users can expand cards to see "Structured Block" details.
         4. Methodology: Explains the extraction and validation phases.
         
         Design Rationale:
         - Dashboard first provides the "Landscape View" (Meta-Analysis).
         - Directory allows the "Deep Dive" (Specific Ideas).
         - Color scheme is low-saturation warm grays for background to reduce eye strain during deep research.
    -->
    
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices:
         - Category Density -> Bar Chart (Chart.js) -> Compare volume of ideas per category.
         - Crowded vs Profitable -> Scatter Plot (Chart.js) -> X=Competitors, Y=Price/Validation.
         - Failure Modes -> Doughnut Chart (Chart.js) -> Visual breakdown of common pitfalls.
         - Idea List -> HTML Grid with JS Filter/Search -> Efficient browsing of text-heavy data.
         - Confirmation: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used.
    -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->

